 thinking that makes liberals say ignorant comments and write articles that do not make sense...Reality is tough to swallow, some will do better than others and trying to use this scenario to &quot;bring up&quot; the level of education for the masses is an ideology that equates to a nightmare!  All things will never be equal!  Tell the children's parents to take responsibility for there own children's futures. As a parent you shouldn't have to make it better for the people who are negligent or their children!  I'm not even a parent and I can see how incredibly foolish this is...Success is usually derived from hard work and the longing for greatness, not because someone else thinks equality prevails!  My Father worked his A off (double shifts) to give both my brother and I an education in a private Catholic school in the heart of a bad neighborhhood, we weren't rich! Some people take life seriously and some people seriously just Take in life! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1253" language="en" documentId="4197" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Ca Zual" date="Aug 29, 2013 5:39PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="18" thumbsDown="0" origId="4197" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1253"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>